    <SCHEME>
      <NAME> Arguments for Mental-World Claims. Evaluative Premiss: Effect </NAME>
      <FORM>
        <PREMISE> P </PREMISE>
        <PREMISE> S's being M is the best explanation of P  </PREMISE>
        <CONCLUSION> S is M </CONCLUSION>
      </FORM>
      <CQ> Is P explained by another mental attribute of S? </CQ>
    </SCHEME>
    <SCHEME>
      <NAME> Arguments for Mental-World Claims. Physical-world Premiss: Cause </NAME>
      <FORM>
        <PREMISE> P </PREMISE>
        <PREMISE> P causes S to be M </PREMISE>
        <CONCLUSION> S is M </CONCLUSION>
      </FORM>
      <CQ> Does anyhting block the occurrence of the event/ state "S is M"? </CQ>
